1. Requirements
  - Purpose or necessity of the use case
2. Data Points
  - Identify all data points where the use case may be present.
  - Example: If the use case is for an alert after 10 login failures within 4 minutes, data points may be 
anywhere a user account can be used to log in.
3. Log Validation
  - Ensure the logs contain pertinent information such as timestamps, user, source, destination etc.
4. Design
  - Condition, aggregation, priority
5. Implementation
6. Documentation
  - SOP for working on alerts. Include an escalation matrix on who to notify for escalation
7. Onboarding
  - Once it is developed and tested, move into production environment
8. Testing
9. Fine Tuning
  - Continually refine and update use case to maintain accuracy and effectiveness
